{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1000,"text":"It's hard to believe that it's less than a year since the extraordinary moment"},{"time":5000,"text":"when the finance, the credit, which drives our economies froze."},{"time":9000,"text":"A massive cardiac arrest."},{"time":12000,"text":"The effect, the payback, perhaps, for years of vampire predators like Bernie Madoff,"},{"time":16000,"text":"whom we saw earlier."},{"time":18000,"text":"Abuse of steroids, binging and so on."},{"time":21000,"text":"And it's only a few months since governments"},{"time":23000,"text":"injected enormous sums of money to try and keep the whole system afloat."},{"time":29000,"text":"And we're now in a very strange sort of twilight zone,"},{"time":31000,"text":"where no one quite knows what's worked, or what doesn't."},{"time":35000,"text":"We don't have any very clear maps, any compass to guide us."},{"time":40000,"text":"We don't know which experts to believe anymore."}]},{"cues":[{"time":43000,"text":"What I'm going to try and do is to give some pointers"},{"time":46000,"text":"to what I think is the landscape on the other side of the crisis,"},{"time":50000,"text":"what things we should be looking out for"},{"time":52000,"text":"and how we can actually use the crisis."},{"time":55000,"text":"There's a definition of leadership which says,"},{"time":57000,"text":"\"It's the ability to use the smallest possible crisis"},{"time":61000,"text":"for the biggest possible effect.\""},{"time":63000,"text":"And I want to talk about how we ensure that this crisis,"},{"time":66000,"text":"which is by no means small, really is used to the full."}]},{"cues":[{"time":70000,"text":"I want to start just by saying a bit about where I'm coming from."},{"time":73000,"text":"I've got a very confused background"},{"time":76000,"text":"which perhaps makes me appropriate for confused times."},{"time":80000,"text":"I've got a Ph.D. in Telecoms, as you can see."},{"time":83000,"text":"I trained briefly as a Buddhist monk under this guy."},{"time":86000,"text":"I've been a civil servant,"},{"time":88000,"text":"and I've been in charge of policy for this guy as well."}]},{"cues":[{"time":91000,"text":"But what I want to talk about begins when I was at this city, this university, as a student."},{"time":96000,"text":"And then as now, it was a beautiful place of balls and punts, beautiful people,"},{"time":102000,"text":"many of whom took to heart Ronald Reagan's comment"},{"time":105000,"text":"that, \"even if they say hard work doesn't do you any harm,"},{"time":108000,"text":"why risk it?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":111000,"text":"But when I was here,"},{"time":113000,"text":"a lot of my fellow teenagers were in a very different situation,"},{"time":117000,"text":"leaving school at a time then of rapidly growing youth unemployment,"},{"time":121000,"text":"and essentially hitting a brick wall in terms of their opportunities."},{"time":125000,"text":"And I spent quite a lot of time with them rather than in punts."},{"time":129000,"text":"And they were people who were not short of wit, or grace or energy,"},{"time":134000,"text":"but they had no hope, no jobs, no prospects."},{"time":137000,"text":"And when people aren't allowed to be useful,"},{"time":139000,"text":"they soon think that they're useless."},{"time":142000,"text":"And although that was great for the music business at the time,"},{"time":145000,"text":"it wasn't much good for anything else."},{"time":147000,"text":"And ever since then, I've wondered why it is that capitalism"},{"time":150000,"text":"is so amazingly efficient at some things, but so inefficient at others,"},{"time":154000,"text":"why it's so innovative in some ways and so un-innovative in others."}]},{"cues":[{"time":159000,"text":"Now, since that time,"},{"time":161000,"text":"we've actually been through an extraordinary boom,"},{"time":164000,"text":"the longest boom ever in the history of this country."},{"time":168000,"text":"Unprecedented wealth and prosperity,"},{"time":170000,"text":"but that growth hasn't always delivered what we needed."},{"time":174000,"text":"H.L. Mencken once said that, \"to every complex problem,"},{"time":177000,"text":"there is a simple solution and it's wrong.\""},{"time":181000,"text":"But I'm not saying growth is wrong,"},{"time":183000,"text":"but it's very striking that throughout the years of growth,"},{"time":186000,"text":"many things didn't get better."},{"time":188000,"text":"Rates of depression carried on up, right across the Western world."},{"time":192000,"text":"If you look at America, the proportion of Americans"},{"time":194000,"text":"with no one to talk to about important things"},{"time":196000,"text":"went up from a tenth to a quarter."},{"time":199000,"text":"We commuted longer to work, but as you can see from this graph,"},{"time":202000,"text":"the longer you commute the less happy you're likely to be."},{"time":206000,"text":"And it became ever clearer that economic growth"},{"time":209000,"text":"doesn't automatically translate into social growth or human growth."}]},{"cues":[{"time":214000,"text":"We're now at another moment"},{"time":216000,"text":"when another wave of teenagers are entering a cruel job market."},{"time":221000,"text":"There will be a million unemployed young people here"},{"time":223000,"text":"by the end of the year,"},{"time":225000,"text":"thousands losing their jobs everyday in America."},{"time":228000,"text":"We've got to do whatever we can to help them,"},{"time":231000,"text":"but we've also got to ask, I think, a more profound question"},{"time":234000,"text":"of whether we use this crisis to jump forward"},{"time":237000,"text":"to a different kind of economy that's more suited to human needs,"},{"time":241000,"text":"to a better balance of economy and society."}]},{"cues":[{"time":245000,"text":"And I think one of the lessons of history is that"},{"time":247000,"text":"even the deepest crises can be moments of opportunity."},{"time":252000,"text":"They bring ideas from the margins into the mainstream."},{"time":255000,"text":"They often lead to the acceleration of much-needed reforms."},{"time":259000,"text":"And you saw that in the '30s,"},{"time":262000,"text":"when the Great Depression paved the way"},{"time":265000,"text":"for Bretton Woods, welfare states and so on."},{"time":269000,"text":"And I think you can see around us now,"},{"time":271000,"text":"some of the green shoots of a very different kind of economy and capitalism"},{"time":274000,"text":"which could grow."},{"time":276000,"text":"You can see it in daily life."},{"time":278000,"text":"When times are hard, people have to do things for themselves,"},{"time":280000,"text":"and right across the world, Oxford, Omaha, Omsk,"},{"time":284000,"text":"you can see an extraordinary explosion of urban farming,"},{"time":287000,"text":"people taking over land, taking over roofs,"},{"time":290000,"text":"turning barges into temporary farms."}]},{"cues":[{"time":292000,"text":"And I'm a very small part of this."},{"time":294000,"text":"I have 60,000 of these things in my garden."},{"time":297000,"text":"A few of these. This is Atilla the hen."},{"time":300000,"text":"And I'm a very small part of a very large movement,"},{"time":303000,"text":"which for some people is about survival,"},{"time":306000,"text":"but is also about values, about a different kind of economy,"},{"time":309000,"text":"which isn't so much about consumption and credit,"},{"time":311000,"text":"but about things which matter to us."},{"time":314000,"text":"And everywhere too, you can see a proliferation of time banks"},{"time":317000,"text":"and parallel currencies,"},{"time":319000,"text":"people using smart technologies to link up"},{"time":322000,"text":"all the resources freed up by the market -- people, buildings, land --"},{"time":325000,"text":"and linking them to whomever has got the most compelling needs."}]},{"cues":[{"time":330000,"text":"There's a similar story, I think, for governments."},{"time":333000,"text":"Ronald Reagan, again, said the two funniest sentences"},{"time":336000,"text":"in the English language are,"},{"time":338000,"text":"\"I'm from the government. And I'm here to help.\""},{"time":342000,"text":"But I think last year when governments did step in,"},{"time":344000,"text":"people were quite glad that they were there, that they did act."},{"time":347000,"text":"But now, a few months on,"},{"time":349000,"text":"however good politicians are at swallowing frogs"},{"time":352000,"text":"without pulling a face, as someone once put it,"},{"time":354000,"text":"they can't hide their uncertainty."},{"time":356000,"text":"Because it's already clear"},{"time":358000,"text":"how much of the enormous amount of money they put into the economy,"},{"time":362000,"text":"really went into fixing the past, bailing out the banks, the car companies,"},{"time":367000,"text":"not preparing us for the future."},{"time":369000,"text":"How much of the money is going into concrete and boosting consumption,"},{"time":373000,"text":"not into solving the really profound problems we have to solve."}]},{"cues":[{"time":377000,"text":"And everywhere, as people think about the unprecedented sums"},{"time":380000,"text":"which are being spent of our money and our children's money,"},{"time":383000,"text":"now, in the depth of this crisis, they're asking:"},{"time":385000,"text":"Surely, we should be using this with a longer-term vision"},{"time":389000,"text":"to accelerate the shift to a green economy,"},{"time":391000,"text":"to prepare for aging, to deal with some of the inequalities"},{"time":394000,"text":"which scar countries like this and the United States"},{"time":398000,"text":"rather than just giving the money to the incumbents?"},{"time":401000,"text":"Surely, we should be giving the money to entrepreneurs, to civil society,"},{"time":404000,"text":"for people able to create the new,"},{"time":406000,"text":"not to the big, well-connected companies,"},{"time":409000,"text":"big, clunky government programs."},{"time":412000,"text":"And, after all this, as the great Chinese sage Lao Tzu said,"},{"time":416000,"text":"\"Governing a great country is like cooking a small fish."},{"time":419000,"text":"Don't overdo it.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":422000,"text":"And I think more and more people are also asking:"},{"time":425000,"text":"Why boost consumption, rather than change what we consume?"},{"time":428000,"text":"Like the mayor of São Paulo who's banned advertising billboards,"},{"time":432000,"text":"or the many cities like San Francisco"},{"time":434000,"text":"putting in infrastructures for electric cars."},{"time":437000,"text":"You can see a bit of the same thing happening in the business world."},{"time":443000,"text":"Some, I think some of the bankers"},{"time":445000,"text":"who have appear to have learned nothing and forgotten nothing."},{"time":448000,"text":"But ask yourselves: What will be the biggest sectors of the economy"},{"time":451000,"text":"in 10, 20, 30 years time? It won't be the ones lining up for handouts,"},{"time":455000,"text":"like cars and aerospace and so on."}]},{"cues":[{"time":457000,"text":"The biggest sector, by far, will be health --"},{"time":460000,"text":"already 18 percent of the American economy,"},{"time":463000,"text":"predicted to grow to 30, even 40 percent by mid-century."},{"time":467000,"text":"Elder care, child care, already much bigger employers than cars."},{"time":471000,"text":"Education: six, seven, eight percent of the economy and growing."},{"time":475000,"text":"Environmental services, energy services, the myriad of green jobs,"},{"time":479000,"text":"they're all pointing to a very different kind of economy"},{"time":482000,"text":"which isn't just about products, but is using distributed networks,"},{"time":487000,"text":"and it's founded above all on care, on relationships,"},{"time":491000,"text":"on what people do to other people, often one to one,"},{"time":494000,"text":"rather than simply selling them a product."}]},{"cues":[{"time":499000,"text":"And I think that what connects the challenge for civil society,"},{"time":502000,"text":"the challenge for governments and the challenge for business now"},{"time":505000,"text":"is, in a way, a very simple one, but quite a difficult one."},{"time":509000,"text":"We know our societies have to radically change."},{"time":513000,"text":"We know we can't go back to where we were before the crisis."},{"time":517000,"text":"But we also know it's only through experiment"},{"time":520000,"text":"that we'll discover exactly how to run a low carbon city,"},{"time":524000,"text":"how to care for a much older population,"},{"time":527000,"text":"how to deal with drug addiction and so on."}]},{"cues":[{"time":531000,"text":"And here's the problem."},{"time":533000,"text":"In science, we do experiments systematically."},{"time":536000,"text":"Our societies now spend two, three, four percent of GDP"},{"time":541000,"text":"to invest systematically in new discovery, in science, in technology,"},{"time":544000,"text":"to fuel the pipeline of brilliant inventions"},{"time":547000,"text":"which illuminate gatherings like this."},{"time":550000,"text":"It's not that our scientists are necessarily much smarter"},{"time":552000,"text":"than they were a hundred years ago, maybe they are,"},{"time":555000,"text":"but they have a hell of a lot more backing than they ever did."},{"time":559000,"text":"And what's striking though,"},{"time":561000,"text":"is that in society there's almost nothing comparable,"},{"time":563000,"text":"no comparable investment,"},{"time":565000,"text":"no systematic experiment, in the things capitalism isn't very good at,"},{"time":569000,"text":"like compassion, or empathy, or relationships or care."}]},{"cues":[{"time":574000,"text":"Now, I didn't really understand that until I met this guy"},{"time":577000,"text":"who was then an 80-year-old, slightly shambolic man"},{"time":580000,"text":"who lived on tomato soup and thought ironing was very overrated."},{"time":585000,"text":"He had helped shape Britain's post-war institutions,"},{"time":588000,"text":"its welfare state, its economy,"},{"time":591000,"text":"but had sort of reinvented himself as a social entrepreneur,"},{"time":594000,"text":"became an inventor of many, many different organizations."},{"time":597000,"text":"Some famous ones like the Open University, which has 110,000 students,"},{"time":602000,"text":"the University of the Third Age, which has nearly half a million older people"},{"time":605000,"text":"teaching other older people,"},{"time":607000,"text":"as well as strange things like DIY garages and language lines"},{"time":612000,"text":"and schools for social entrepreneurs."},{"time":614000,"text":"And he ended his life selling companies to venture capitalists."}]},{"cues":[{"time":618000,"text":"He believed if you see a problem, you shouldn't tell someone to act,"},{"time":621000,"text":"you should act on it yourself, and he lived long enough"},{"time":623000,"text":"and saw enough of his ideas first scorned and then succeed"},{"time":627000,"text":"that he said you should always take no as a question and not as an answer."},{"time":633000,"text":"And his life was a systematic experiment to find better social answers,"},{"time":637000,"text":"not from a theory, but from experiment, and experiment involving the people"},{"time":642000,"text":"with the best intelligence on social needs,"},{"time":644000,"text":"which were usually the people living with those needs."},{"time":646000,"text":"And he believed we live with others, we share the world with others"},{"time":649000,"text":"and therefore our innovation must be done with others too,"},{"time":653000,"text":"not doing things at people, for them, and so on."}]},{"cues":[{"time":657000,"text":"Now, what he did didn't used to have a name,"},{"time":661000,"text":"but I think it's rapidly becoming quite mainstream."},{"time":664000,"text":"It's what we do in the organization named after him"},{"time":667000,"text":"where we try and invent, create, launch new ventures,"},{"time":670000,"text":"whether it's schools, web companies, health organizations and so on."},{"time":674000,"text":"And we find ourselves part of a very rapidly growing global movement"},{"time":678000,"text":"of institutions working on social innovation,"},{"time":681000,"text":"using ideas from design or technology or community organizing"},{"time":685000,"text":"to develop the germs of a future world, but through practice and through demonstration"},{"time":690000,"text":"and not through theory."},{"time":693000,"text":"And they're spreading from Korea to Brazil to India to the USA"},{"time":696000,"text":"and across Europe."},{"time":699000,"text":"And they've been given new momentum by the crisis, by the need for better answers"},{"time":705000,"text":"to joblessness, community breakdown and so on."}]},{"cues":[{"time":708000,"text":"Some of the ideas are strange."},{"time":710000,"text":"These are complaints choirs."},{"time":712000,"text":"People come together to sing about the things that really bug them."},{"time":715000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":717000,"text":"Others are much more pragmatic: health coaches, learning mentors, job clubs."},{"time":721000,"text":"And some are quite structural, like social impact bonds"},{"time":724000,"text":"where you raise money to invest in diverting teenagers from crime"},{"time":728000,"text":"or helping old people keep out of hospital,"},{"time":730000,"text":"and you get paid back according to how successful your projects are."}]},{"cues":[{"time":736000,"text":"Now, the idea that all of this represents,"},{"time":738000,"text":"I think, is rapidly becoming a common sense"},{"time":741000,"text":"and part of how we respond to the crisis,"},{"time":743000,"text":"recognizing the need to invest in innovation for social progress"},{"time":747000,"text":"as well as technological progress."},{"time":749000,"text":"There were big health innovation funds"},{"time":752000,"text":"launched earlier this year in this country,"},{"time":754000,"text":"as well as a public service innovation lab."},{"time":756000,"text":"Across northern Europe, many governments"},{"time":758000,"text":"now have innovation laboratories within them."},{"time":761000,"text":"And just a few months ago, President Obama"},{"time":763000,"text":"launched the Office of Social Innovation in the White House."}]},{"cues":[{"time":766000,"text":"And what people are beginning to ask is:"},{"time":768000,"text":"Surely, just as we invest in R and D, two, three, four percent,"},{"time":772000,"text":"of our GDP, of our economy,"},{"time":774000,"text":"what if we put, let's say, one percent of public spending"},{"time":777000,"text":"into social innovation, into elder care, new kinds of education,"},{"time":781000,"text":"new ways of helping the disabled?"},{"time":783000,"text":"Perhaps we'd achieve similar productivity gains in society"},{"time":787000,"text":"to those we've had in the economy and in technology."}]},{"cues":[{"time":791000,"text":"And if, a generation or two ago, the big challenges"},{"time":793000,"text":"were ones like getting a man on the moon,"},{"time":796000,"text":"perhaps the challenges we need to set ourselves now"},{"time":799000,"text":"are ones like eliminating child malnutrition, stopping trafficking,"},{"time":804000,"text":"or one, I think closer to home for America or Europe,"},{"time":806000,"text":"why don't we set ourselves the goal"},{"time":808000,"text":"of achieving a billion extra years of life for today's citizens."},{"time":811000,"text":"Now those are all goals which could be achieved within a decade,"},{"time":815000,"text":"but only with radical and systematic experiment,"},{"time":819000,"text":"not just with technologies, but also with lifestyles and culture"},{"time":823000,"text":"and policies and institutions too."}]},{"cues":[{"time":827000,"text":"Now, I want to end by saying a little bit about what I think this means for capitalism."},{"time":833000,"text":"I think what this is all about, this whole movement"},{"time":835000,"text":"which is growing from the margins, remains quite small."},{"time":838000,"text":"Nothing like the resources of a CERN or a DARPA or an IBM or a Dupont."},{"time":842000,"text":"What it's telling us is that capitalism is going to become more social."},{"time":846000,"text":"It's already immersed in social networks."},{"time":848000,"text":"It will become more involved in social investment, and social care"},{"time":853000,"text":"and in industries where the value comes from what you do with others,"},{"time":857000,"text":"not just from what you sell to them,"},{"time":860000,"text":"and from relationships as well as from consumption."},{"time":863000,"text":"But interestingly too, it implies a future where society learns a few tricks from capitalism"},{"time":868000,"text":"about how you embed the DNA of restless continual innovation"},{"time":872000,"text":"into society, trying things out and then growing and scaling the ones that work."}]},{"cues":[{"time":879000,"text":"Now, I think this future will be quite surprising to many people."},{"time":883000,"text":"In recent years, a lot of intelligent people thought that capitalism had basically won."},{"time":888000,"text":"History was over"},{"time":890000,"text":"and society would inevitably have to take second place to economy."},{"time":895000,"text":"But I've been struck with a parallel in how people often talk about capitalism today"},{"time":900000,"text":"and how they talked about the monarchy 200 years ago,"},{"time":903000,"text":"just after the French Revolution and the restoration of the monarchy in France."}]},{"cues":[{"time":907000,"text":"Then, people said monarchy dominated everywhere"},{"time":910000,"text":"because it was rooted in human nature."},{"time":912000,"text":"We were naturally deferential. We needed hierarchy."},{"time":915000,"text":"Just as today, the enthusiasts of unrestrained capitalism"},{"time":919000,"text":"say it's rooted in human nature,"},{"time":921000,"text":"only now it's individualism, inquisitiveness, and so on."},{"time":924000,"text":"Then monarchy had seen off its big challenger, mass democracy,"},{"time":929000,"text":"which was seen as a well-intentioned but doomed experiment,"},{"time":932000,"text":"just as capitalism has seen off socialism."},{"time":935000,"text":"Even Fidel Castro now says that the only thing worse"},{"time":938000,"text":"than being exploited by multinational capitalism"},{"time":940000,"text":"is not being exploited by multinational capitalism."},{"time":945000,"text":"And whereas then monarchies, palaces and forts dominated every city skyline"},{"time":949000,"text":"and looked permanent and confident,"},{"time":951000,"text":"today it's the gleaming towers of the banks which dominate every big city."}]},{"cues":[{"time":955000,"text":"I'm not suggesting the crowds are about to storm the barricades"},{"time":958000,"text":"and string up every investment banker from the nearest lamppost,"},{"time":962000,"text":"though that might be quite tempting."},{"time":964000,"text":"But I do think we're on the verge of a period when,"},{"time":967000,"text":"just as happened to the monarchy and, interestingly, the military too,"},{"time":971000,"text":"the central position of finance capital is going to come to an end,"},{"time":975000,"text":"and it's going to steadily move to the sides, the margins of our society,"},{"time":979000,"text":"transformed from being a master into a servant,"},{"time":982000,"text":"a servant to the productive economy and of human needs."}]},{"cues":[{"time":986000,"text":"And as that happens,"},{"time":988000,"text":"we will remember something very simple and obvious about capitalism,"},{"time":991000,"text":"which is that, unlike what you read in economics textbooks,"},{"time":994000,"text":"it's not a self-sufficient system."},{"time":997000,"text":"It depends on other systems,"},{"time":999000,"text":"on ecology, on family, on community,"},{"time":1002000,"text":"and if these aren't replenished, capitalism suffers too."},{"time":1006000,"text":"And our human nature isn't just selfish, it's also compassionate."},{"time":1011000,"text":"It's not just competitive, it's also caring."},{"time":1016000,"text":"Because of the depth of the crisis, I think we are at a moment of choice."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1021000,"text":"The crisis is almost certainly deepening around us."},{"time":1024000,"text":"It will be worse at the end of this year,"},{"time":1026000,"text":"quite possibly worse in a year's time than it is today."},{"time":1029000,"text":"But this is one of those very rare moments"},{"time":1032000,"text":"when we have to choose whether we're just pedaling furiously"},{"time":1035000,"text":"to get back to where we were a year or two ago,"},{"time":1038000,"text":"and a very narrow idea of what the economy is for,"},{"time":1042000,"text":"or whether this is a moment to jump ahead, to reboot"},{"time":1047000,"text":"and to do some of the things we probably should have been doing anyway."},{"time":1050000,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1052000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}